  "articleSummary": "**Summary:**  \nThe article argues that modern developers are the most vulnerable “credential warehouses,” and a single careless click can expose every secret on a laptop, turning a local breach into a full‑scale supply‑chain compromise. It critiques vague “be careful” advice and instead proposes concrete, high‑leverage defenses: run all development work inside isolated DevContainers (or similar containers), tightly limit mounted home directories, and seed the environment with aggressive canary‑token tripwires to detect credential access instantly. The piece is written as a pragmatic, slightly urgent tutorial for software engineers, DevOps teams, and security‑conscious managers, using the recurring metaphor of a warehouse filled with valuable keys and the visual “blueprint” infographic to frame its six‑step mitigation strategy.",
